## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

- **Recommended voice:** Warm, knowledgeable friend — part gift editor, part nail enthusiast
- **Tone characteristics:**
  - Direct and decisive — tells the reader what to buy and why, no hedging
  - Warm without being saccharine — acknowledges the emotion of gifting without overdoing it
  - Practically helpful — answers the "is this right for her?" question before the reader has to ask
  - Gently urgent — Mother's Day window is real; the post creates forward momentum without manufactured panic
- **Language style:** Use "she" and "her" naturally when describing the recipient. Use "you" for the gifter. Avoid nail-tech jargon unless explained inline (HEMA, RPM). British English spelling throughout. No em dashes. No banned vocabulary.
- **Audience match:** Gifters are motivated by love but guided by practicality. A tone that says "here's exactly what to choose and why she'll love it" converts better than a flat spec list. Mums shopping for themselves respond to the self-care angle and the value framing.

